metadata.name: Tapestry #1
metadata.description:
Tapestry celebrates palettes and texture. It emphasizes the power of palettes by using them in a unique texture with infinite variations.

Tapestry has 136 very distinct palettes, each with it's own (not so secret) backstory.

The mint size of 747 was chosen because that is the expected number of mints required to get at least one of each palette. For anyone interested, this is called the coupon collector problem and has an accurate approximate solution of n * (ln(n) + .577216) + 0.5

Algorithm

The patterns and colors are generated by using parameterized Perlin noise, and a custom algorithm is used for the canvas-like texture. The canvas texture was especially satisfying since it is generated very fast by manipulating the z values with trigonometric functions. This allows Tapestry to render efficiently on any screen size (see the Responsive section below).

Attributes

Palette - each palette has an equal chance of being selected.
Amplitude - determines the overall turbulence in the pattern.
Vertical Variation - the variation in the vertical component of the pattern.
Horizontal Variation - the variation in the horizontal component of the pattern.
Noise Factor - the amount of noise the the overall pattern.
Color Variation - the variation in the color changes.

Rarities

The minting process will sort out the rarities. Since there are only 747 mints for 136 palettes, there will most certainly be some very rare palettes, probably a few with only one mint.

The other attributes produce billions of variations, virtually guaranteeing that each pattern will be entirely unique.

Responsive

Tapestry is responsive and will render on any screen size. Due to it's rendering speed, it's well suited for 4K or larger screens.

Notes

's' saves an image using the exact size of the current window so you can get an image in any resolution.

Since displays vary so widely and Tapestry will work on any any screen size, you can tweak the grain and brightness using the left/right arrow keys (grain), and up/down arrow keys (brightness). 'r' resets the values to the defaults.

metadata.name: Suspension #7
metadata.description:
Suspension uses simple objects to create structures suspended in space, held together by relation and composition.

The unique composition algorithm is random enough to produce infinite variations, but ordered enough to produce engaging artworks that are instantly recognizable.

Suspension uses negative space, additive coloring, and a unique rendering technique to create a very distinct style. 

It has many hand tuned palettes, with rare palettes that produce incisive variations.

Suspension is responsive and will render fast at any resolution. It looks great on wide screens of 2K, 4K or larger.

To accommodate the variation in displays, you can use the up/down arrow keys to adjust the brightness. 'r' resets to the default values.

's' will save an image in the exact size of the window, so you can create images in any resolution.

metadata.name: Organicon, variation 00 - special edition #28
metadata.description:
Thank you!

Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
One of 640 special edition generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation 00 is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. A small counter in the lower-right corner displays the progress.

Interface: on first load the piece operates in active mode. In this mode an iteration is cleared 30s after completion and replaced by the next iteration. This mode is indicated by a flashing dot in the upper-right corner.

A first mouse click disables active mode. The current iteration will complete and remain on screen. A second mouse click clears the screen, loads the next iteration, and reenables active mode.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #455
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.
